
[1]thinking

   THINK'ING, ppr. Having ideas; supposing; judging; imagining; intending;
   meditating.

   1. a. Having the faculty of thought; cogitative; capable of a regular
   train of ideas.

   Man is a thinking being.

              THINK'ING, n. Imagination; cogitation; judgment.

   I heard a bird so sing,

   Whose music, to my thinking, pleas'd the king.
